      "title": "India\u2019s Imports of Russian Oil Set for New Record High",
      "summary": "India is set to import a record-high volume of Russian crude in June as the Hormuz crisis and the U.S. waivers on Russia\u2019s barrels have pushed the world\u2019s third-largest crude importer to gorge on Moscow\u2019s oil again. India has imported 2.6 million barrels per day (bpd) of Russian crude oil so far in June, according to preliminary vessel-tracking data from commodity analytics firm Kpler cited by Indian media. So far this month, Russian crude has accounted for as much as 53.5% of all Indian oil imports, per the data.\u00a0 \u00a0\u2026",
